		<!-- tnm 10/19/2018:  Unsure who Hr Oberartz is, since it's a German word in the Danish text it seems like perhaps an unofficial title, so unsure whether to tag as "gebhard" or "doctorHead." how to handle [sic] in line 32, 53, 56 - turn into translator/editor's note? -->
	</teiHeader>
	<text>
		<body>

			<div type="original">

				<div type="opener">
					<p>
						<add place="pageTopLeftCorner" type="insertion" rend="upside-down">Naar jeg nu kommer godt fra det kan jeg gifte mig om nogen vil have mig </add>
						<note type="editor" source="kj mb">Written upside down in top, left corner of letter.</note>
					</p>
					<p>
						<hi rend="underline">Sondag<note type="translator">[sic]</note>
						</hi>
					</p>
					<!-- tnm 2018-10-14: this underline doesn't appear in the docx translation, but it's in the image. How to handle [sic] above?-->
					<p>24 Juli 1931 <placeName key="dresden">Dresden</placeName>
					</p>
				</div>
				<!-- end "opener(original)" div -->

				<div type="body">
					<p style="salutation">Kære Fru <persName key="garlandM">Maria Garland</persName>
					</p>
					<p>Vær sød at lade mig vide, hvordan det gaar med Bogen og Deres Mands Arbejde. Jeg er saa spændt derpaa. Jeg ligger stadig i Sengen efter mit frygtelige Operation, og ingen svarer paa mit daglige Spørgsmaal, om jeg snart maa komme op. Og Professoren er meget stræng.</p>
					<!-- tnm 2018-10-14: how to handle spacing within the lines? copied from .docx but a series of spaces seems like a bad idea for rendering into html -->
					<p>
						<persName key="?">Hr. Oberartz</persName>
						<note type="translator">German for "head doctor"</note> er saa munter og sød imod mig. Sig det til Deres Mand. Jeg tror, <persName key="wegenerG">Fru Gerda</persName> i sit Manuskript siger noget jeg ikke saa gerne vilde have sagt i Bogen. I dag har man baaret mig ud i <placeName key="womensClinicGarden"> Haven</placeName> paa en Baar [sic] for at jeg skal faa Sol og se Naturen, det er saa dejligt.
					</p>
				</div> <!-- end body(original) div -->

				<div type="closer">
					<p>Vær sød og send mig et Par Ord. Jeg beder Dem hilse Deres Lillemor og Søn og de alle hjærteligste<note type="translator">[sic]</note> Hilsner til Dem</p>
					<p style="valediction">fra Deres</p>
					<p>
						<hi rend="underline">
							<persName key="lili">Lili Elbe</persName>
						</hi>
					</p>
				</div> <!-- end closer(original) div -->
			</div> <!-- end original div> -->

			<div type="translation">

				<div type="opener">
					<p>
						<add place="pageTopLeftCorner" type="insertion" rend="upside-down">When I get better I can marry if anyone will have me </add>
						<note type="editor" source="kj mb">Written upside down in top, left corner of letter.</note>
					</p>
					<p>
						<hi rend="underline">Sunday</hi>
					</p>
					<!-- this underline doesn't appear in the docx translation, but it's in the image. -->
					<p>24 July 1931 <placeName key="dresden">Dresden</placeName>
					</p>
				</div>
				<!-- end "opener(original)" div -->

				<div type="body">
					<p style="salutation">Dear Mrs. <persName key="garlandM">Maria Garland</persName></p>
					<p>Please let me know how it is going with the book and your husband’s work. I am so excited about that. I am still lying in bed after my terrible operation and noone answers my daily question if I can get up soon. And the professor is very strict.</p>
					<p>
						<persName key="?">The chief physician</persName>
						<note type="translator">German for "head doctor"</note> is so cheerful and sweet with me. Tell that to your husband. I believe in her manuscript <persName key="wegenerG">Mrs. Gerda</persName> says something I would prefer not to have said in the book. Today they have carried me out in <placeName key="womensClinicGarden">the garden</placeName> on a stretcher in order for me to get sun and see nature, it is so lovely.
					</p>
					<!-- not sure how the above translator's note should appear in english version -->
				</div> <!-- end body(original) div -->

				<div type="closer">
					<p>Please send me a few words. I ask you to greet your sweet little mother and son and all the heartiest greetings to you</p>
					<p style="valediction">from your</p>
					<p>
						<hi rend="underline">
							<persName key="lili">Lili Elbe</persName>
						</hi>
					</p>
				</div> <!-- end closer(original) div -->
			</div>
			<!-- end original div> -->
		</body>
	</text>
